nodes.title: SMOOSH V2 BY @JEFFJAG
widgets_values:
Well, it's time for a refresh.

SMOOSH v2

Updated with IPAdapter so the images get smooshed in 3 ways: 

IPAdapter (mini lora) in the Model
Clip Encoding in Conditioning
Encoded via VAE to Latent

This one requires a lot of plugins and nodes, specifically: 
- ComfyUI Manager
- ComfyUI IPAdapter plus
- WAS Node Suite
- Derfuu ComfyUI Modded Nodes
- Comfyui Art Venture (Color Correct)

The Models required for SDXL version of IPAdapter:
- sd_xl_base_1.0.safetensors - base model (no refiner needed)
- ip-adapter_sdxl.bin - ipadapter model
- model.safetensors - renamed to model(sdxl).safetensors - because it's the SDXL version of clip vision

nodes.title: EDITABLE FIELDS
widgets_values:
Encode IPAdapter Image
- Noise - more noise here will make your images cleaner, if you like that kind of thing
- Weight - to adjust the strength of each input

Image Width and Height
- Please pick SDXL compatible sizes/aspect for the base generation if you want faces that have regular amount of facial features.
- ON the second pass, there is a complicated system of blending the latent from the first pass with the encoded results from the first pass. The Second Pass size will be limited by your available VRAM or other hardware variables. Adjust as needed.

Apply IPAdapter from Encoded
- Weight set at 1 which is high strength, but the "end_at" is set to 0.75 which means after 3/4 of the way through, it switches off the ipadapter and only uses the text prompt. You can use this variable to either turn the IPAdapter all the way on/off or some variable in between. The lower (0.33) the more strength will be the Text Prompt, and the higher the end_at (0.75), the more it uses IPAdapter

LoRA - If no LoRA is needed, right click and select "Bypass" on this node

Color Correct - You can adjust the results of the 1st pass here with some basic color correction to save a step in the Photo Editor of your choice.

KSampler 1st pass
- Steps (anything above 40)
- CFG (I like 4-10 in this side) If you're not doing faces or anything like that, feel free to crank it up higher.
- denoise ( 0.5 - 0.6 worked for me)

KSampler 2nd pass
- Steps (anything)
- CFG (I usually aim for "less than double" whatever I put in 1st pass) - Larger resolution means there's more room for higher values
- denoise (lower will be closer to your original so it'll be a more faithful upscale, but since this is an interpretive upscale process, I recommend going 0.48 to 0.6 here so you'll get more detail and variation on top of the 1st pass

Have fun, check out my work on X: @jeffjag 
or on my site:  https://jeffjag.ai
